sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Operator as CodeFlare Operator<br/>(manager)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CASecret as CA Secret
    participant InitCont as Init Container<br/>(head/worker)
    participant RayHead as Ray Head<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker<br/>10001/TCP gRPC

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 1: RayCluster OAuth Dashboard Access (OpenShift)
    User->>Router: GET /dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuth: Forward (Reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    Note right of OAuth: Validates OpenShift<br/>OAuth token
    OAuth->>Dashboard: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8265 (localhost)
    Dashboard-->>OAuth: Dashboard HTML
    OAuth-->>Router: Response (TLS)
    Router-->>User: Dashboard page (HTTPS)

    Note over Operator,RayWorker: Flow 2: RayCluster mTLS Certificate Bootstrap
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create CA Secret<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Secret created
    Operator->>CASecret: Store RSA 2048-bit CA<br/>self-signed, 1yr validity
    Note right of InitCont: Pod starts with<br/>CA secret volume mount
    InitCont->>InitCont: Generate server cert<br/>via OpenSSL CLI<br/>signed by cluster CA
    RayHead->>RayWorker: gRPC communication<br/>10001/TCP, mTLS<br/>per-pod certificates
    RayWorker-->>RayHead: Response (mTLS)

    Note over RayHead,RayWorker: Flow 3: Network Policy Enforcement
    Note right of RayHead: NetworkPolicy rules:<br/>1. Same-cluster pods: full access<br/>2. Same-namespace: 10001, 8265<br/>3. KubeRay ns: 8265, 10001<br/>4. openshift-monitoring: 8080<br/>5. All sources: 8443 (OAuth),<br/>   10001 (mTLS secured)
